  <main class="container">
    <section>
      <h2>Understanding Data Privacy</h2>
      
      <div class="definition-box">
        <h3>What is Data Privacy?</h3>
        <p>Data privacy, also known as information privacy, is the aspect of information technology that deals with the ability an organization or individual has to determine what data in a computer system can be shared with third parties.</p>
      </div>
      
      <p>Data privacy is essential for managing and protecting personal data. It ensures that consumers' information is collected and used in a way that respects their rights and maintains their trust.</p>
      
      <div class="quote-box">
        <p>"Privacy is not something that I'm merely entitled to, it's an absolute prerequisite." — Marlon Brando</p>
      </div>
      
      <h3>Why Data Privacy Matters</h3>
      <div class="key-points">
        <ul>
          <li><i class="fa-icon fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Protects against unauthorized access and misuse</li>
          <li><i class="fa-icon fas fa-check-circle"></i> Maintains accuracy of personal information</li>
          <li><i class="fa-icon fas fa-handshake"></i> Builds trust in digital services</li>
          <li><i class="fa-icon fas fa-balance-scale"></i> Complies with regulations like GDPR and CCPA</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Privacy by Design Principles</h2>
      
      <div class="definition-box">
        <h3>Privacy by Design</h3>
        <p>Privacy by Design is an approach to systems engineering which takes privacy into account throughout the whole engineering process. The concept was developed in the 1990s and has since been formalized in privacy legislation around the world.</p>
      </div>
      
      <ul class="standard-list">
        <li><strong>Proactive not Reactive:</strong> Prevent privacy issues before they occur</li>
        <li><strong>Privacy as Default:</strong> Automatic protections without user action</li>
        <li><strong>Embedded Design:</strong> Privacy built into systems from the start</li>
        <li><strong>Full Functionality:</strong> Achieves privacy without sacrificing other objectives</li>
        <li><strong>End-to-End Security:</strong> Protection throughout data lifecycle</li>
        <li><strong>Transparency:</strong> Clear policies and independent verification</li>
        <li><strong>User Respect:</strong> Prioritizes user interests and control</li>
      </ul>
      
      <div class="quote-box">
        <p>"The right to privacy is a fundamental human right that underpins freedom of association, thought and expression, as well as freedom from discrimination." — United Nations</p>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <h2>Data Protection Techniques</h2>
      
      <div class="key-points">
        <ul>
          <li><i class="fa-icon fas fa-lock"></i> Encryption of sensitive data</li>
          <li><i class="fa-icon fas fa-user-shield"></i> Access controls and authentication</li>
          <li><i class="fa-icon fas fa-mask"></i> Data anonymization techniques</li>
          <li><i class="fa-icon fas fa-clipboard-check"></i> Regular privacy audits</li>
          <li><i class="fa-icon fas fa-hourglass-half"></i> Data retention policies</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

